This side features irregular shapes and organic textures, adding an element of decay and unease.The structure itself is a merging of different elements: it has the clean lines and geometric forms typical of Yoshida’s work but with the rough, almost sculptural texture from Beksiński. The marble side glows faintly under the low-angle light, creating a striking contrast with the shadowy, almost sinister left side.In the background, there are hazy, distant cityscapes or perhaps distant galaxies, blending the real and the surreal, further enhancing the sci-fi atmosphere.
